The paper discusses meta-learning algorithms for quickly adapting to new tasks, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on first-order meta-learning algorithms, which use only first-order derivatives for the meta-learning updates. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper applies these algorithms to few-shot classification tasks, which are commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper provides theoretical analysis of the algorithms, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
